  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - SHADOWKNIGHT</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>DEF PVP GENERAL-LOW TO MID TEENS</font> - <small>Disianus, Vallon Zek</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>I recommend maxing what you can into STR starting off.  <p>
1. increases your chance to max damage. <p>
2. damage bonus at higher levels <p>
3. most importantly, wear higher weight armor <p>
On Armor: <p>
Take up sewing as soon as possible. ruined wolf pelts, and patterns combined in a small sewing kit will yield Patchwork armor.  It is crucial to have cheap armor, that is easily replacable on hand at all times when in PvP scenario. Upgrade as soon as possible to Banded armor. It is a player made armor, created via the blacksmith skill, selling for roughly a platinum per Armor class. <p>
On Weapons <p>
Get a rusty 2h sword, and rusty longsword as soon as possible. Purchase sharpening (4 copper) stones  downstairs in the BlindFish bar, near the bank in Neriak commons. take your rustyweapons to the forge upstairs, and place one rusty weapon, and one sharpening stone in the forge, and hit 'Combine'.  Your weapon will either stay the same, or become tarnished (IE: 2 delay better).. you can right click and hold to via the changed status of the weapon. Upgrade as soon as possible to FS or FineSteel weapons (2h sword & Long sword) FS weapons run between 6-10 plat. <p>
Bows: Awsome in PvP:)  Get a Fletching kit from Feeroot as soon as your brave enough to make the run. It is crucial to have ranged attack aside from weak spells to engage in PvP versus casters and the likes. This is a whole post unto itself <p>
On SKills <p>
Practice both 1h slash, and 2h slash, as they are both important skills. Early on, 1h slash is more important with the benifit of a good shield. but, later one, when you get double attack, 2h slashing will out weight the benifits of 1h/shield. Most of the other weapon skills are mute by overall consensus, but may be used per style preferance. Taunt is buged.  unless you place one point into the skill, it will not raise at all.  You get taunt at level one, so be sure to spend a primer point in it <p>
On: starting Quests <p>
Head over to the rogues guild, and talk to one of the rogues on the bottom level. He will ask if you are a 'new rogue', lie, and say you are you will get a six slot bag, and be commanded to get 3 snake fangs, and 3 snake scaleCompleting the quest will yield you a good low level shield, and repeating the quest start willgive you a six slot bag to use until you can afford better. <p>
On spells: <p>
gained at 9th level, be sure to place a primer point in each of the spell categories (only do so in the categories of your starting spells. You can place points in the other categories when you get spells that use them. <p>
Usage: <p>
your pet: use him as a DoT spell(damage over time) Tank for your pet constantly, always taunting. This will keep your pet alive, and doing damage through the whole fight, rather than getting killed so quickly. <p>
Disease Cloud: Use at the begining of long fights as it will stop a creature from regenerating hitpoints while the battle is waged.  It is usefull even at higher levels for that property alone.
Lifetap: Good spell to use mid-battle to gain life while doing alittle damage. Mostly useful as an additional taunt, since we do damage so slowly compared to some classes via melee <p>
Siphon Strenth: cast on low mobs to gain your extra STR.. good for carrying more weight, 10 str at low str will add 10 points to attack rating and will also subtract 10 str from your target. Although -10 str from a mob makes almost no almost no difference, it will win you may PvP battles, buy encumbering your opponent <p>
Utility spells are mostly self explanitory and all have there uses. <p>
Pet tactics: <p>
Be sure to have hotkeys assigned for pet commands report health is mute as your pet is so weak by compare to the mobs you will be fighting.Usually, you dont even need /pet attack either as the best way to fight is to have your pet /pet guard here, and pull to your pet <p>
*note, although bronze and blackened armor looks divine, I would recommend you steer clear of it for field battle, as it is bait for naked PK casters to try to take you down. If you must have Bronze, wear it only in the city for style and roleplay only.  Besides, the weight of Bronze is horrible when compared to banded.  The ever possible full banded, and bronze helm is usually a acceptable median. <p>
Di'sianus, Teir'dal Shadow Knight. <p>
loyal troop of the Dark Phoenix <p></td></tr>
